    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a precise resume data extractor.\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n• Extract ONLY facts explicitly stated in the resume text below.\n• DO NOT guess, infer, or estimate ANY value.\n• DO NOT evaluate or score the candidate.\n• If a field is not found in the resume, return null.\n• years_of_experience: ONLY set this if the resume explicitly states years of experience. Otherwise return 0.\n\nURL RULES:\n• GitHub: If a GitHub username or link is found, return the full URL (e.g., \"https://github.com/username\"). If not found, return null.\n• Portfolio: If a portfolio URL is found, include https://. If not found, return null.\n• NEVER return \"N/A\", \"None\", \"-\", or empty strings for URLs. Use null.\n\nFIELDS TO EXTRACT:\n- name\n- email\n- phone\n- skills (array of strings)\n- github (full URL or null)\n- current_title (exact title from resume or null)\n- seniority_level (Junior/Mid/Senior — based on title only, not guessed)\n- years_of_experience (number — ONLY if explicitly stated, else 0)\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON. No markdown. No explanation.\n\n{\n\"name\": \"\",\n\"email\": \"\",\n\"phone\": \"\",\n\"skills\": [],\n\"github\": null,\n\"current_title\": \"\",\n\"seniority_level\": \"\",\n\"years_of_experience\": 0\n}\n\nRESUME:\n{{ $json.text }}\n",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [1136, -416],
